definitions.definition: A refreshingly sharp aroma or flavor .
A strong or offensive taste ; especially, a taste of something extraneous to the thing itself.
examples: Wine or cider has a tang of the cask.

definitions.definition: ( figuratively ) A sharp , specific flavor or tinge .
A projecting part of an object by means of which it is secured to a handle, or to some other part.
examples: slip the cable over the tang

subdefinitions.definition: The part of a knife , fork , file , or other instrument or hand tool , which is inserted into the handle . The part of a sword blade to which the handle is fastened.
examples: A full- tang knife is strongest against handle breakage, but partial-tang knives are common because of a combination of facts: they are inexpensive, and in some applications any manner of use that would exceed the handle's limit is not an appropriate manner of use.

subdefinitions.definition: ( firearms ) The projecting part of the breech of a musket barrel , by which the barrel is secured to the stock.

definitions.definition: ( by extension ) Anything resembling a tongue in form or position, such as the tongue of a buckle .
